Arg. 1. If Angels in Singing do the Will of God, do that which is pleaſing and acceptable to God, and in ſo doing worſhip God;
then Singing, or to ſing, is the Will of God, well-pleaſing to him, and is acceptable in his ſight, and is a part of his Worſhip. But Angels, in Singing, do the Will of God, do that which is well-pleaſing to him, and acceptable in his ſight,
• and in ſo doing they worſhip him. Ergo, To ſing, is to do the Will of God, 'tis well-pleaſing to him, and acceptable in his ſight, and in ſo doing we worſhip him.

